==English==

===Etymology===
From Late {{etyl|enm}} {{term|benefytt|lang=enm}}, {{term|benefett|lang=enm}}, alteration (due to {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|bene-|lang=la}}) of {{etyl|enm}} {{term|benfet|lang=enm}}, {{term|bienfet|lang=enm}}, {{term|bienfait||good or noble deed|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|benfet||well-done|lang=xno}}, {{etyl|frm}} {{term|bienfait|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|bienfet|lang=fro}}, {{term|bienfait||foredeal, favour|lang=fro}}, from past participle of {{etyl|fro}} {{term|bienfaire||to do good, do well|lang=fro}}, from {{term|bien||well|lang=fro}} + {{term|faire||to do|lang=fro}}, modelled after {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|benefactum||good deed|lang=la}}. More at {{l|en|benefactor}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈbɛn.ə.fɪt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-benefit.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[advantage]], [[help]] or [[aid]] from something.
# A [[payment]] made in [[accordance]] with an [[insurance]] [[policy]] or a [[public]] [[assistance]] [[scheme]].
# A [[performance]], etc, given to [[raise]] [[fund]]s for some [[cause]].

====Synonyms====
* (''advantage, help''): [[foredeal]], [[advantage]], [[aid]], [[assistance]], [[boon]], [[help]]
* (''payment''): [[subsidy]]

====Antonyms====
* (''advantage, help''): [[disadvantage]], [[encumbrance]], [[hindrance]], [[nuisance]], [[obstacle]], [[detriment]]

